rk-merge-and-pr/", "title": "Fork, merge and PR", "content_html": "<h1>Fork, merge and PR</h1>", "image": null, "date_published": "2025-04-05T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [{"name": "Xiaochuan Yang"}], "tags": ["TIL", "dev tools"]}, {"id": "https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/02/15/survive/", "url": "https://xiaochuany.github.io/blog/2025/02/15/survive/", "title": "The Cox survival guide: hazards, models and time", "content_html": "<h1>The Cox survival guide: hazards, models and time</h1>\n<p>!!! abstract\n    This note is an overview of survival analysis with a focus on the Cox proportional hazards model, a key tool for modelling time-to-event data. We define hazard functions, address right-censoring, and derive estimators like Nelson-Aalen and Kaplan-Meier. The Cox model's semiparametric form and partial likelihood estimation are discussed, along with evaluation metrics such as concordance probability.</p>", "image": null, "date_published": "2025-02-15T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [{"name": "Xiaochuan Yang"}], "tags": ["Technical", "survival analysis"]}]}